The paper proposes a semantic SLAM framework that utilizes object-level semantic constraints, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. The paper also presents a data association and optimization framework, which is a core component of robotics (RO) and involves mathematical optimization. The paper's focus on semantic labeling and map representation also suggests a connection to natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.RO, cs.CV, and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI and cs.CL.
